<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1057] casts in TBinaryProtocol.tcc causing &quot;dereferencing type-punned pointer will break strict-aliasing rules&quot; warnings from gcc </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1057</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Code is doing things like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;uint8_t b[2];
uint16_t val;

val = *(int16_t*)b;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Due to aliasing there isn&apos;t a guarantee that b[] will be placed on a 16 bit boundary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix is to use unions to ensure alignment. Patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
